Package com.landawn.abacus.util

Class Seq<T,E extends Exception>

java.lang.Object
com.landawn.abacus.util.Seq<T,E>
Type Parameters:
T - the type of the elements in this stream
E - the type of the checked exception this sequence can throw
All Implemented Interfaces:
Immutable, AutoCloseable
@Beta @SequentialOnly @Immutable public final class Seq<T,E extends Exception> extends Object implements AutoCloseable, Immutable
The sequence class is an abstract class that represents a sequence of elements and supports different kinds of computations. The sequence operations are divided into intermediate and terminal operations, and are combined to form sequence pipelines.

The sequence will be automatically closed after a terminal method is called/triggered

Seq can be easily transformed to Stream by the transformB methods

Refer to com.landawn.abacus.util.stream.BaseStream and com.landawn.abacus.util.stream.Stream for more APIs docs.

    • splitByChunkCount

      public static <T, E extends Exception> Seq<T,E> splitByChunkCount(int totalSize, int maxChunkCount, boolean sizeSmallerFirst, Throwables.IntBiFunction<? extends T,? extends E> mapper)
      Splits the total size into chunks based on the specified maximum chunk count.
      The size of the chunks can be either smaller or larger first based on the flag.
      The length of returned sequence may be less than the specified maxChunkCount if the input totalSize is less than maxChunkCount. 
       
 final int[] a = Array.rangeClosed(1, 7);
 splitByChunkCount(7, 5, true, (fromIndex, toIndex) ->  copyOfRange(a, fromIndex, toIndex)); // [[1], [2], [3], [4, 5], [6, 7]]
 splitByChunkCount(7, 5, false, (fromIndex, toIndex) ->  copyOfRange(a, fromIndex, toIndex)); // [[1, 2], [3, 4], [5], [6], [7]]
      Type Parameters:
      T - the type of the elements in the resulting stream
      E - the type of the exception that might be thrown
      Parameters:
      totalSize - the total size to be split. It could be the size of an array, list, etc.
      maxChunkCount - the maximum number of chunks to split into
      sizeSmallerFirst - if true, smaller chunks will be created first; otherwise, larger chunks will be created first
      mapper - a function to map the chunk from and to index to an element in the resulting stream
      Returns:
      a sequence of the mapped chunk values
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if totalSize is negative or maxChunkCount is not positive.
      See Also:
      • Stream.splitByChunkCount(int, int, boolean, IntBiFunction)

    • transform

      @Beta @IntermediateOp public <U> Seq<U,E> transform(Function<? super Seq<T,E>,Seq<U,E>> transfer)
      Transforms the current sequence into another sequence by applying the provided function. The function takes the current sequence as input and returns a new sequence.

      Seq.defer(Supplier) can be used to avoid eager loading by terminal operations invoked in transfer. For example: 
       
     seq.transform(s -> Seq.defer(() -> s.(..).someTerminalOperation(...)));
      Type Parameters:
      U - The type of elements in the returned stream.
      Parameters:
      transfer - The function to be applied on the current sequence to produce a new stream.
      Returns:
      A new sequence transformed by the provided function.
      Throws:
      IllegalStateException - if the sequence has already been operated upon or closed.
      See Also:
      • transformB(Function)
      • transformB(Function, boolean)
      • sps(Function)
      • sps(int, Function)
